Italian Premier Giuseppe Conte sits at the Senate in Rome on Tuesday ahead of a second confidence vote on his coalition government. Conte Monday won the first of two mandatory confidence votes on his four-day-old coalition of rival parties after a day of fielding insults during a boisterous Parliament session from an opposition outraged that Italy got a new government instead of a new election. Photo: AP  
